  "prompt": "What is the best comedy movie ever?",
  "response": "The \"best\" comedy movie is subjective and can vary greatly depending on personal taste, cultural background, and sense of humor. However, there are several comedy films that are widely acclaimed and have stood the test of time. Here are a few that are often cited as contenders for the title:\n\n1. **\"Some Like It Hot\" (1959)** - Directed by Billy Wilder, this classic film stars Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, and Jack Lemmon in a story about two musicians who disguise themselves as women to escape from mobsters.\n\n2. **\"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\" (1975)** - This British comedy from the Monty Python group is a parody of the Arthurian legend and is known for its absurd humor and quotable lines.\n\n3. **\"Airplane!\" (1980)** - A spoof of disaster movies, \"Airplane!\" is packed with slapstick humor and visual gags that have influenced the parody genre.\n\n4. **\"This Is Spinal Tap\" (1984)** - Directed by Rob Reiner, this mockumentary about a fictional British rock band is a cult classic, beloved for its deadpan portrayal of the music industry.\n\n5. **\"Groundhog Day\" (1993)** - Starring Bill Murray, this film about a weatherman reliving the same day over and over again has become synonymous with the concept of time loops in popular culture.\n\n6. **\"The Big Lebowski\" (1998)** - Directed by the Coen Brothers, this film follows \"The Dude\" as he gets entangled in a complex kidnapping plot, with a mix of surreal and stoner humor.\n\n7. **\"Bridesmaids\" (2011)** - This female-led comedy, written by and starring Kristen Wiig, was a critical and commercial success, praised for its portrayal of friendship and its groundbreaking approach to women in comedy.\n\n8. **\"The Grand Budapest Hotel\" (2014)** - Directed by Wes Anderson, this visually stunning film combines a quirky narrative with a unique comedic style.\n\n9. **\"Booksmart\" (2019)** - Directed by Olivia Wilde, this teen comedy has been lauded for its fresh take on the coming-of-age genre and its strong performances.\n\nUltimately, the best comedy movie is one that resonates with you personally and makes you laugh the hardest. It's worth exploring different eras and styles of comedy to find the film that proves to be your favorite.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
